==English==

===Etymology===
Hindi ''pańkhā'' ‘fan’, from Sanskrit [[पकशक]] ''pakśaka'', from [[पकश]] ''pakśa'' ‘wing’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'pʌŋkə/}}, {{IPA|/'pʌŋkɑ:/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a large [[fan]] on the Indian subcontinent, especially made from a [[leaf]], or made from [[cloth]] as designed to cool a room
#:*'''1973''': Perhaps it was a mistake to invite Mr Stanhope; the day was intolerably hot and humid; all he wanted to do was to lie on his bed with a '''punkah''' sighing over him, at least moving the unbreathable air. — Patrick O'Brian, ''HMS Surprise''